      • has

        EObjectQueryStepBuilder<S> has(java.lang.String eStructuralFeatureName,
                               java.lang.Object value)
        Filters all EObjects in the result set that have the given feature set to the given value.

        Any EObject that is an instance of an EClass which does not define any EAttribute or EReference with the given name will be discarded and filtered out.

        For determining the feature, EClass.getEStructuralFeature(String) is used per EObject individually.

        The value will be compared via Objects.equals(Object, Object).

        Parameters:
        eStructuralFeatureName - The name of the EStructuralFeature to filter by. Must not be null.
        value - The value to filter by. May be null.
        Returns:
        The query builder, for method chaining. Never null.

      • has

                               java.lang.Object value)
        Filters all EObjects in the result set that have the given feature set to the given value.

        Any EObject that belongs to an EClass that does not support the given feature will be discarded and filtered out.

        The value will be compared via Objects.equals(Object, Object).

        Parameters:

        value - The value to filter by. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The query builder, for method chaining. Never null.

      • isInstanceOf

        EObjectQueryStepBuilder<S> isInstanceOf(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass eClass)
        Filters all EObjects that are an instance of the given EClass.

        This method also considers polymorphism, i.e. instances of Sub-EClasses will pass this filter as well.

        This operation is null-safe. Any null values will be discarded and filtered out.

        Parameters:
        eClass - The EClass to filter by. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The query builder, for method chaining. Never null.

      • isInstanceOf

        EObjectQueryStepBuilder<S> isInstanceOf(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass eClass,
                                        boolean allowSubclasses)
        Filters all EObjects that are an instance of the given EClass.

        This operation is null-safe. Any null values will be discarded and filtered out.

        Parameters:
        eClass - The EClass to filter by. Must not be null.
        allowSubclasses - Whether or not subclasses are allowed. If false, any EObject that passes the filter must be a direct instance of the given EClass. If true, EObjects that pass the filter can be a direct or transitive instance of the given EClass.
        Returns:
        The query builder, for method chaining. Never null.

      • eGet

        UntypedQueryStepBuilder<S,java.lang.Object> eGet(java.lang.String eStructuralFeatureName)
        Performs a EObject.eGet(EStructuralFeature) operation on all EObjects in the current result and forwards the result of this method.

        If a given EObject does not have the EStructuralFeature set (i.e. EObject.eIsSet(EStructuralFeature) returns false), then no value will be passed onwards. In any other case, the returned value is passed onwards, even if that value is null.

        Parameters:
        eStructuralFeatureName - The name of the EStructuralFeature to get the value(s) for. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The query builder, for method chaining. Never null.

      • allReferencingEObjects

        EObjectQueryStepBuilder<S> allReferencingEObjects()
        Navigates from an EObject to all other EObjects that reference it.

        This means walking backwards all EReference instances that have the current EObject as target. This method will include the eContainer.

        Returns:
        The query builder, for method chaining. Never null.

      • distinct

        EObjectQueryStepBuilder<S> distinct()
        Description copied from interface: QueryStepBuilder
        Eliminates all duplicated values from the current result.

        This method is lazy, but requires to keep track of the "already encountered" elements in a set. Therefore, RAM consumption on this method may be high if it is applied on very large result sets.

        Specified by:
        distinct in interface QueryStepBuilder<S,org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject>
        Returns:
        The distinct step builder, for method chaining. Never null.
